organic_results.title: University prestige and first-time undergraduate migration in the United States
organic_results.snippet: It is estimated that about one-fourth of the first-time undergraduates in the major American universities in 1963 were interstate migrants, although this varied by type of university. In private non-denominational institutions, for example, about two-thirds were interstate migrants. The purpose of this paper is to indicate the extent to which university prestige accounted for migration to the major American universities in 1963.
